result.execSummary:
The defendant Ontario Jenkins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court will consider motion for expungement in 1 year if defendant pays the fine, has no further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause, provides verification that he has completed 25 hours of community service and has no new reports of firearm possession.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1: Court sentences defendant to serve 3 days in the House of Correction with credit for 3 days, consecutive to any other sentence, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $150.00 plus all applicable court costs, fees and surcharges by 11/28/16 or the nonpayment penalty will be immediate entry of a civil judgment.  Cash bail to apply.  Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

Court will consider motion for expungement in 1 year if defendant pays the fine, has no further violations of the law raising to the level of probable cause, provides verification that he has completed 25 hours of community service and has no new reports of firearm possession.

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Pretrial Incarceration Credit received and filed.

Defendant Ontario Jenkins in court with attorney Ann M Heaps.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Case calendared for plea/sentencing hearing.

AS TO COUNT 1: Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire, addendum and elements received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.

AS TO COUNT 2: Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed and read-in to case for the purposes of sentencing.

Defendant Ontario Jenkins in court with attorney Ann M Heaps.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.

Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance.  Defendant IS Public Defender eligible.
